Modifications from the original Nezha Monitoring project:

Agent:
- Removed: interactive edit command, auto-update (go-github-selfupdate),
  remote config push, server transfer, IOStream (terminal/file manager/
  intranet penetration), MCP, urfave/cli framework dependency
- Added: SSRF protection (probe_guard.go), ICMP rate limiting,
  goroutine leak fix for gRPC unary calls, GitHub proxy acceleration
  for install scripts, self-contained service command restoration
- Changed: switched from urfave/cli to stdlib flag for CLI parsing,
  cleaned go.mod residual dependencies, restored nezhahq/service for
  systemd/Windows Service/launchd management

Dashboard:
- Removed: OAuth2 authentication, alert notifications (Telegram/DingTalk/
  Bark/Email), IOStream server-side, MCP server, command execution,
  server transfer, forced update, NAT traversal, terminal access,
  file manager, frp integration
- Added: modernc.org/sqlite (pure Go SQLite, no CGO required),
  command-line arguments restoration (-v, -c, -db)
- Changed: simplified permissions controller, cleaned task model,
  removed unused RPC methods

Install Scripts:
- Added: self-contained install.sh and install.ps1 for Agent,
  self-contained install.sh for Dashboard with Docker support,
  GitHub public proxy acceleration for China region
- Changed: removed external script repository dependency (nezhahq/scripts),
  removed Gitee mirror, replaced with GitHub public proxies

Docker:
- Added: multi-stage Dockerfile (frontend download -> Go compile -> runtime),
  Dockerfile.prebuilt for pre-compiled binaries, docker-compose.yaml,
  build-docker.ps1 for Windows cross-compile + Linux server packaging

